list.name: Crocubot
list.about: Crocubot is a character in Rick and Morty who is a fusion of a crocodile and a robot. This hybrid creature possesses the physical attributes and instincts of a crocodile, combined with the technological enhancements and abilities of a robot. Crocubot serves as a reminder of the show's penchant for bizarre and unexpected combinations, fusing two seemingly incompatible entities into a single entity. The inclusion of Crocubot adds to the visual diversity of the show's characters and exemplifies its ability to create unique and imaginative beings within the multiverse.

list.name: Cronenberg Rick
list.about: Cronenberg Rick is a version of Rick Sanchez from an alternate reality where the entire population of Earth has transformed into grotesque and mutated beings known as Cronenbergs. Unlike the traditional version of Rick, Cronenberg Rick is a compassionate and remorseful character who feels responsible for the disastrous transformation of his world. His inclusion showcases the show's willingness to explore darker and more introspective themes, providing a contrast to the often irreverent and nihilistic nature of the series. Cronenberg Rick's character offers a glimpse into the consequences of Rick's actions and the potential for redemption and growth within the multiverse.

list.name: Cronenberg Morty
list.about: Cronenberg Morty is a character in Rick and Morty who exists in the same alternate reality as Cronenberg Rick. As a result of the Cronenberg transformation, Cronenberg Morty has also undergone physical changes and now resembles the mutated beings of his world. Cronenberg Morty's character embodies the show's exploration of the consequences of Rick's actions and the collateral damage caused by his scientific experiments. His inclusion adds a touch of tragedy to the show's multiverse, reminding viewers of the far-reaching implications of Rick's actions and the potential for unintended consequences.

list.name: Cult Leader Morty
list.about: Cult Leader Morty is a character in Rick and Morty who becomes the leader of a cult in an alternate reality. His charismatic personality and ability to manipulate others have allowed him to amass a devoted following. Cult Leader Morty's character embodies the show's exploration of power dynamics and the dark side of influence and leadership. His inclusion serves as a satirical commentary on cults and the dangers of blindly following charismatic leaders. Cult Leader Morty showcases the show's ability to tackle complex social issues and explore the impact of power dynamics within the multiverse.

list.name: Cyclops Morty
list.about: Cyclops Morty is a character in Rick and Morty who possesses a single large eye in the center of his forehead, resembling the mythological cyclops. His unique physical appearance sets him apart from other versions of Morty and adds to the show's visual diversity. Cyclops Morty's inclusion showcases the show's ability to introduce variations of characters that challenge conventional norms and expectations. Despite his distinct appearance, Cyclops Morty remains relatable and serves as a reminder that even the most unique individuals can experience the same trials and tribulations as their counterparts.

list.name: Cyclops Rick
list.about: Cyclops Rick is a character in Rick and Morty who, like Cyclops Morty, possesses a single large eye in the center of his forehead. This physical feature sets him apart from other versions of Rick and adds to the show's exploration of visual diversity within the multiverse. Cyclops Rick's inclusion exemplifies the show's ability to reimagine familiar characters in unique ways, showcasing the creative freedom afforded by the concept of infinite realities. Despite his distinct appearance, Cyclops Rick retains the intelligence and wit commonly associated with the character, highlighting the show's emphasis on character traits transcending physical appearances.

list.name: Cynthia
list.about: Cynthia is a character in Rick and Morty who exists in the same alternate reality as her duplicate counterpart, also named Cynthia. Despite their shared identity, the two Cynthias have distinct personalities and aspirations. Cynthia is an embodiment of the show's exploration of the multiplicity of identity and the infinite possibilities within the multiverse. Her inclusion serves as a reminder that even seemingly identical individuals can have unique experiences and perspectives. Cynthia's character adds depth to the show's exploration of identity and the complexities of existence across the vastness of the multiverse.

list.name: Dale
list.about: Dale is a character in Rick and Morty who appears in the episode 'Close Rick-Counters of the Rick Kind.' He is a resident of the Citadel of Ricks and is depicted as a timid and nervous individual. Dale's character represents the more ordinary and relatable side of the show's multiverse, contrasting with the grandiose and eccentric personas of other characters. His inclusion offers a glimpse into the lives of regular individuals within the Citadel and adds a touch of realism to the show's fantastical setting. Dale serves as a reminder that even in the midst of cosmic adventures, everyday people navigate their own struggles and insecurities.

list.name: Daron Jefferson
list.about: Daron Jefferson is a character in Rick and Morty who appears in the episode 'The Ricklantis Mixup.' He is a politician in the Citadel of Ricks and is portrayed as an ambitious and charismatic figure. Daron Jefferson's character serves as a commentary on political power and the corruption that often accompanies it. His inclusion showcases the show's ability to tackle complex social and political issues within its sci-fi framework. Daron Jefferson's story arc within the Citadel offers a satirical exploration of power dynamics and the inherent flaws of political systems, providing a thought-provoking narrative within the show's multiverse.

list.name: David Letterman
list.about: David Letterman is a real-life television host and comedian who makes a cameo appearance in Rick and Morty. In the episode 'The Ricks Must Be Crazy,' Letterman appears as himself, hosting a talk show within a microverse created by Rick. His inclusion adds a touch of meta-humor to the show, blurring the lines between fiction and reality. David Letterman's cameo exemplifies the show's ability to seamlessly incorporate real-world references and personalities into its absurd and fantastical universe. His appearance offers a moment of comedic relief and adds an unexpected layer to the show's humor.

list.name: Davin
list.about: Davin is a character in Rick and Morty who appears in the episode 'The Wedding Squanchers.' He is Summer's boyfriend and is depicted as a typical teenager. Davin's character represents the ordinary and mundane aspects of Morty's life outside of his interdimensional adventures. His inclusion offers a contrast to the show's extraordinary and often chaotic escapades, grounding the narrative in familiar human experiences. Davin serves as a reminder that Morty, despite his grand adventures, still navigates the complexities of adolescence and relationships in his everyday life.

list.name: Diablo Verde
list.about: Diablo Verde is a character in Rick and Morty who appears in the episode 'Something Ricked This Way Comes.' He is the owner of a cursed antique shop and serves as the primary antagonist of the episode. Diablo Verde's character embodies the show's exploration of morality and the consequences of one's actions. His inclusion showcases the show's ability to create compelling and morally ambiguous characters within its comedic framework. Diablo Verde's arc offers a cautionary tale and serves as a reminder that even in the fantastical world of Rick and Morty, actions have consequences.

list.name: Diane Sanchez
list.about: Diane Sanchez is a character in Rick and Morty who is the mother of Beth Smith and the daughter of Rick Sanchez. She is depicted as a complex and troubled individual, with a strained relationship with both her daughter and father. Diane's character serves as a representation of the familial dynamics and emotional baggage present within Morty's family. Her inclusion adds depth to the show's exploration of the Smith family's dynamics and the impact of Rick's presence on their lives. Diane's story arc offers a glimpse into the emotional complexities of the show's characters and adds a layer of emotional depth to the series.

list.name: Dipper and Mabel Mortys
list.about: Dipper and Mabel Mortys are characters in Rick and Morty who exist in a parallel reality where the show Gravity Falls is the dominant theme. They are Morty's counterparts from this reality and closely resemble the characters Dipper and Mabel from Gravity Falls. The inclusion of Dipper and Mabel Mortys serves as a crossover and homage to the popular animated series Gravity Falls, created by Alex Hirsch. This crossover showcases the show's ability to reference and celebrate other works of fiction while maintaining its distinct style and humor. Dipper and Mabel Mortys add a touch of nostalgia for fans of both shows and create a playful connection between the two universes.

list.name: Tuberculosis
list.about: Tuberculosis is a character in Rick and Morty who exists in a post-apocalyptic reality known as the Post-Apocalyptic Dimension. He is depicted as a mutated creature with the appearance of a humanoid virus. Tuberculosis's character represents the show's exploration of the grotesque and monstrous aspects of the multiverse. His inclusion adds to the show's ability to create visually striking and unsettling characters that embody the darker side of existence. Tuberculosis serves as a reminder that within the infinite possibilities of the multiverse, there are realities where destruction and chaos reign.

list.name: Gonorrhea
list.about: Gonorrhea is a character in Rick and Morty who, similar to Tuberculosis, exists in the Post-Apocalyptic Dimension. He is another mutated creature, representing a grotesque manifestation of the sexually transmitted infection. Gonorrhea's character highlights the show's ability to explore uncomfortable and taboo topics through its unique lens. His inclusion serves as a darkly comedic commentary on the consequences of irresponsible behavior and the potential for unexpected outcomes within the multiverse. Gonorrhea embodies the show's irreverent and boundary-pushing nature, offering a stark contrast to traditional portrayals of sexually transmitted infections.

His inclusion serves as a reminder of the potential dangers and threats that exist within different realities. Hepatitis A's portrayal showcases the show's ability to transform even the most mundane and commonplace elements of our world into twisted and unsettling entities within the multiverse.

He represents the infamous disease known as the Bubonic Plague in a humanoid form. Bubonic Plague's character adds to the show's exploration of the grotesque and macabre aspects of the multiverse. His inclusion serves as a reminder of the devastating impact of historical pandemics and the fragility of human existence. Bubonic Plague's portrayal showcases the show's ability to infuse dark humor into even the most tragic and somber subjects, creating a unique blend of satire and introspection within the multiverse.
